iText is a powerful library for creating and manipulating PDF files in Java. To set metadata in a PDF file using iText, you can use the `PdfFileReader` class to read the file, then use the `PdfWriter` class to write the file with the new metadata. Here's an example of how to set the title and author of a PDF file using iText:

1. First, import the necessary classes from iText:
```java
import com.itextpdf.text.Document;
import com.itextpdf.text.pdf.PdfFileReader;
import com.itextpdf.text.pdf.PdfWriter;
```
2. Next, read the PDF file into a `PdfFileReader` object:
```java
PdfFileReader reader = new PdfFileReader(new File("myfile.pdf"));
```
3. Use the `PdfFileReader` to get the document object:
```java
Document document = PdfWriter.getDocument(reader);
```
4. Set the title and author of the document using the `PdfWriter` object:
```java
document.setTitle("My Title");
document.setAuthor("John Doe");
```
5. Write the modified document back to the same file:
```java
PdfWriter writer = PdfWriter.getInstance(document, new FileOutputStream("myfile.pdf"));
document.open();
document.addPage();
writer.write(document);
document.close();
```
This will set the title and author of the PDF file to "My Title" and "John Doe", respectively. You can also use the `PdfReader` and `PdfStamper` classes to read and modify the metadata of a PDF file, respectively.

